   А лл     One night Maloin, a switchman at a seaside railway station   лл А
   А лл     situated by a ferry harbour, witnesses a terrible event.     лл А
   А лл     He is just watching the arrival of the last ferry at night   лл А
   А лл     from his control room on top of a high iron traverse from    лл А
   А лл     where he can see the whole bay. Suddenly he notices that     лл А
   А лл     the first of the disembarking passengers, a tall thin        лл А
   А лл     figure (a certain Brown as it will turn out later) leaves    лл А
   А лл     the harbour, but not on the usual route: after getting       лл А
   А лл     through customs, he goes around the dock and then withdraws  лл А
   А лл     into a dark corner, waiting. Opposite him, in front of the   лл А
   А лл     ship, another man soon appears and throws a suitcase towards лл А
   А лл     the man on the shore. He goes and picks it up, then waits    лл А
   А лл     in an even darker corner for the other man to join him.      лл А
   А лл     When he arrives, however, they begin to quarrel and finally, лл А
   А лл     in the course of the vehement fight, due to a hit that       лл А
   А лл     turns out to be fatal, the shorter one falls in the water    лл А
   А лл     and sinks, clutching the suitcase in his hand. Maloin is     лл А
   А лл     watching the scene, astonished. Finally, in a state of fear  лл А
   А лл     and shock, he opens the door of his control room, but the    лл А
   А лл     sharp and loud creaking sound disturbs and frightens away    лл А
   А лл     the murderer. Brown is forced to flee before being able to   лл А
   А лл     fish out the suitcase from the water. After the murderer     лл А
   А лл     disappears down one of the streets behind the harbour,       лл А
   А лл     Maloin cautiously climbs down from his cabin to the shore.   лл А
   А лл     When he realises that there is nothing he can do for the     лл А
   А лл     victim, he dredges up the suitcase. He takes it up to his    лл А
   А лл     control room and opens it: it is packed with money. He is    лл А
   А лл     dazzled. He does not go either to call the police or fetch   лл А
   А лл     the murderer; he just stares at the pile of money. He        лл А
   А лл     simply cannot believe his eyes. Then, after meticulously     лл А
   А лл     drying and counting the banknotes, he hides the suitcase     лл А
   А лл     in his closet and locks it. At dawn, when his colleague      лл А
   А лл     arrives, he acts as if nothing had happened. He returns      лл А
   А лл     home on his usual route. Nevertheless, this path is not the  лл А
   А лл     same anymore                                                 лл А
